transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hey, Paul, this is K.T. Goodrich from Pfizer Score Blue.

Speaker 2: Bear with me as I pull up your account with your telephone number.

Speaker 1: As I read off your chart when I pull that up, just help me verify some things.

Speaker 2: So I can help you put a stop to that. All right, bud?

Speaker 1: Yeah, man.

Speaker 2: All right, bud. Thanks very much.

Speaker 1: So when I read your chart, I see that you are working with Dr. Moore Holcomb, Pat?

Speaker 2: No, you got the wrong guy.

Speaker 1: Before you go any further, you picked up the wrong line here.

Speaker 2: Huh. Pat?

Speaker 1: Yes, Pat.

Speaker 2: Yeah, that's what I meant, Pat.

Speaker 1: You're working with Dr. Moore Holcomb.

Speaker 2: Yeah, Moore Holcomb is our Pfizer doctor, and it looks like she set you up

Speaker 1: with the prescription and the VIP status for, just correct me if I'm wrong,

Speaker 2: the AGV Viagra, the white diet pill that we make in our Pfizer-Lazenfrancis,

Speaker 1: FDA-approved one.

Speaker 2: But I see that Dr. Moore Holcomb has ordered the pharmacy to send you refills

Speaker 1: on her behalf.

Speaker 2: Do you want me to put a stop to that so you're not getting those monthly anymore?

Speaker 1: I want you to reverse the charge that happened today or yesterday

Speaker 2: and also cancel the rest of them, too.

Speaker 1: Okay, so that's hard for me to do, and I'll tell you why.

Speaker 2: Wait a minute, wait a minute.

Speaker 1: Wait, stop for just a minute.

Speaker 2: I already sent you all an email right after I placed the order.

Speaker 1: Did you get a reply for the email?

Speaker 2: No, you didn't.

Speaker 1: Nobody replied, but I did send it, and I need you to reverse the charge for today,

Speaker 2: and I don't care why.

Speaker 1: I don't even care why it's difficult to do.

Speaker 2: You don't care?

Speaker 1: Why?

Speaker 2: It doesn't matter because it's only an excuse, you know.

Speaker 1: So all I need you to do is I already asked you all to –

Speaker 2: I simply asked you all not to auto-refill this order,

Speaker 1: and I made it clear I was only doing a test to see how your product worked.

Speaker 2: Well, it didn't, and it's not a really good product.

Speaker 1: So I definitely don't want it again.

Speaker 2: And I need you to reverse the charge, please.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: So I let you speak, Pat, and I'm just working with you.

Speaker 1: This is the first time we ever met and we talked.

Speaker 2: So I'm only trying to explain to you I'm going to start the credit process now,

Speaker 1: okay, like you asked, and what I'm seeing is that the product went out.

Speaker 2: It's being shipped.

Speaker 1: There's a tracking number on it.

Speaker 2: And then when it hits you, though, please refuse the package.

Speaker 1: That way it gets back to us, and then I'll complete all the reverse of charges.

Speaker 2: Are you there?

Speaker 1: It's breaking up.

Speaker 2: I'm still here.

Speaker 1: I'm still here.

Speaker 2: I'm just trying to figure out what it is you're trying to bill me for.

Speaker 1: No, okay.

Speaker 2: I didn't order anything.

Speaker 1: Okay, so you're rehashing this.

Speaker 2: Am I being recorded, sir?

Speaker 1: No, I'm not recording you, but you're not listening to what I'm saying to you.

Speaker 2: No, with both my ears, sir, I listen to you,

Speaker 1: but you're breaking up with your connection or something.

Speaker 2: You want to call back, sir, when you got a bad connection?

Speaker 1: No, I don't want to call back.

Speaker 2: I want you to take care of it.

Speaker 1: Yeah, so this is how I'm going to take care of it because this is our process.

Speaker 2: So I just need you to be kind, and it takes strength to be kind.

Speaker 1: It's easy to be weak and fly off.

Speaker 2: I know your gears are grinded.

Speaker 1: I'm upset, too, for you, but I didn't do this, okay?

Speaker 2: The doctor ordered the pharmacy to send you a refill.

Speaker 1: You didn't communicate with the doctor, and I'm just telling you what I see.

Speaker 2: So what I'm doing now is I'm putting a stop.

Speaker 1: I'm going to put you on hold.

Speaker 2: I'm going to put a stop to all the monthly refills and all that.

Speaker 1: I'm going to override the system.

Speaker 2: There's a package being sent to you right now, so I'm trying to explain that.

Speaker 1: Do you have a pen and paper on you,

Speaker 2: or do you want to go in the dashboard so you can locate the number

Speaker 1: so I can explain to you the return to sender?

Speaker 2: I'm going to start the credit process now, but are you with me still?

Speaker 1: You have my email address?

Speaker 2: Yeah, I'm not going to email you.

Speaker 1: That's why I'm asking if you have a pen.

Speaker 2: I'm not going to email you because I don't have access to that.

Speaker 1: I'm only on phone calls.

Speaker 2: But let me do the first things first.

Speaker 1: Let me put you on a brief hold, and I'll put a stop to this,

Speaker 2: and I'll do as you wish, and I'll start the credit process.

Speaker 1: All right, Pat?

Speaker 2: And let's start again on the right foot.

Speaker 1: I'm not here to clash with you.

Speaker 2: I'm here to support you.

Speaker 1: We're Americans here, and, you know, Americans look out for each other.

Speaker 2: We don't bully each other.

Speaker 1: You know what I mean?

Speaker 2: Look out for each other.

Speaker 1: That's how we roll.

Speaker 2: All right?

Speaker 1: Stand by.

Speaker 2: I'm ready for the address.

Speaker 1: Okay, your address is 4062 Omron Drive, right?

Speaker 2: It is.

Speaker 1: Okay, so there's a package being sent to you for that charge.

Speaker 2: All you have to do is, when you get that package,

Speaker 1: write refuse return to sender and drop it in the USPS blue box.

Speaker 2: And we already have a tracking number on it that you sent back to us.

Speaker 1: I'm starting the credit process.

Speaker 2: All right?

Speaker 1: So let me put you on a brief hold so I can process this for you, okay?

Speaker 2: I'll take care of you, bud.

Speaker 1: One moment.

Speaker 2: Thank you.

Speaker 1: Thank you.

Speaker 2: Thank you.
